Consider the following code:

```
reg foobar = 0;
always @(posedge clk) begin
    foobar <= some_complex_expression_here;
end

assign foobar = 1;
```

Yosys will silently ignore the "assign" statement. This should probably result in a "multiple drivers" error instead: A given identifier can be either combinatorially or synchronously assigned, but not both.

